.row.row-grid.align-items-center.pb-5
  .col-md-6.order-md-1
    img.img-fluid.rounded.shadow-lg.transform-perspective-left(src='assets/img/webs.jpeg' alt='app mockup')
  .col-md-6.order-md-2
    .pr-md-5
      h3 Website Development
      p
        | This website was created using modern web development best practices, frameworks and tools.
      #accordion10.mt-5
        .card
          #headingOne.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseOne' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseOne')
                | <b>1 </b>Development Tools
          #collapseOne.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingOne' data-parent='#accordion10')
            .card-body
              ul
                li <code>Git </code> - Used for version control and triggering the continuous integration (CI) pipeline
                li <code>VSCode </code> - IDE used to write the source code
                li <code>Sketch & Photoshop </code> - Create graphic assets (ie. logo)
        .card
          #headingTwo.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseTwo' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseTwo')
                | <b>2 </b>Frontend Development
          #collapseTwo.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingTwo' data-parent='#accordion10')
            .card-body
              ul
                li <code>Pug </code> - A high-performance template engine used to markup DOM elements 
                li <code>Sass </code> - A superset of CSS to write expressive style markup
                li <code>ES7/ES2017 </code> - Newest ECMAScript standard to leverage latest Javascript capabilities available on modern browsers
                li <code>Babel </code> - To transpile ES7 code to JS and polyfill functions that not available on older browsers 
                li <code>Webpack 4 </code> - Module bundler for transforming, bundling, or packaging the source code and assets to obtain the build files
                li <code>Yarn </code> - Node package manager to install third-party node packages
                li <code>Bootstrap 4 </code> - Frontend CSS framework for rapid prototyping and development of the UI
        .card
          #headingThree.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseThree' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseThree')
                | <b>3 </b>Continuous Integration/ Deployment (CICD)
          #collapseThree.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingThree' data-parent='#accordion10')
            .card-body
              p.text-muted To keep with best practices, the final build files are not checked into the git repository. Instead, a CICD pipeline was set-up (using Github Actions) to automatically build from source files and deploy to Github Pages when each commit is pushed to Github. This way the source repository is not polluted with temporary build files and no additional effort/time is needed to deploy the website with each release or commit.
        .card
          #headingThree.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseThree44' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseThree44')
                | <b>4 </b>Code Quality
          #collapseThree44.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingThree' data-parent='#accordion10')
            .card-body
              p.text-muted In order to maintain code quality, code linters were used. They look for syntax errors and inconsistencies in the code.
              ul
                li <code>StyleLint </code> - Linter for Sass/CSS files
                li <code>ESLint </code> - Linter for JS files

