      h3 Domain Setup
      p
        | These are the series of steps needed to setup a custom domain
      #accordion20.mt-5
        .card
          #headingOne.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseOne' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseOne')
                | <b>1 </b>Buy a domain from a registrar
          #collapseOne.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingOne' data-parent='#accordion20')
            .card-body
              | Decide on an available domain name that is descriptive of the website, easy to remember. You will have the choice to register the domain on several different top-level domains if available such as <code> .com, .org, .biz, and .net </code>.
              | Visit a domain name registrar such as <code>namecheap.com, Domain.com</code> and input the chosen domain name. Ensure that the chosen registrar is also GDPR compliant.
        .card
          #headingTwo.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseTwo' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseTwo')
                | <b>2 </b>Configure the domain on Github
          #collapseTwo.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingTwo' data-parent='#accordion20')
            .card-body
              | To set up a www or custom subdomain, such as <code>www.example.com</code> or <code>blog.example.com</code>, you must create a CNAME file in your site's repository with your custom domain in the root folder.
        .card
          #headingThree.card-header
            h5.mb-0
              button.btn.btn-link.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#collapseThree' aria-expanded='false' aria-controls='collapseThree')
                | <b>3 </b>Configure the DNS settings
          #collapseThree.collapse(aria-labelledby='headingThree' data-parent='#accordion20')
            .card-body
              | Navigate to your DNS provider and create a CNAME record that points your subdomain to the default domain for your site. For example, if you want to use the subdomain www.example.com for your user site, create a CNAME record that points <code>www.example.com</code> to <code>\<user\>.github.io</code>. For more information about how to create the correct record, see your DNS provider's documentation.        